body_content.explanation: a national park (= a large area of land protected by the government because of its natural beauty or because it has a special history) in the US state of California:
examples: Redwood Creek's bridges are in the backcountry of Redwood National Park and allow for easier access to several backcountry campsites.
Two amateur naturalists discovered the three giants deep inside Redwood National Park this summer after inspecting 95 percent of the trees in the forest.
